24/03/2004
BUERGENSTOCK, Switzerland -- Four-party talks on reunifying Cyprus will begin Wednesday (24 March) in Switzerland.
Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul is on hand, as is Mehmet Ali Talat, prime minister of the "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" and Greek Cypriot leader Tassos Papadopoulos.
Greece is also sending a representative.
The talks are aimed at reaching a solution to the Cyprus problem before 1 May, when the Greek Cypriot part of the island becomes a member of the EU.
UN Secretary General Kofi Annan is expected to step in and resolve any continuing disputes after this round of talks.
(Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, AFP - 23/03/04)
